 class=title> <A HREF=http://pub29.ezboard.com/ukonjur.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Konjur</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 67<br> <font color=#A0B0E0>(4/3/01 2:57:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub29.ezboard.com/fsilverhawksofdrinalfrm37.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Should we have an active Treasury - read the post!</span><hr size=1> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>When I first joined, I talked in guildchat and posted a message here about forming a guild treasury replete with money and items.  <br>
<br>
I was patted on the head, asked to calm down, and instructed simply to ask for help from fellow silver hawks who would surely help me should the need ever arise for a short term loan.  I was highly encouraged to DROP the subject as it would cause upheaval and dissention.<br>
<br>
A few nights ago, I sold an 18k BP for a friend who was going to share some of the profits with me.  The buyer had some REALLY nice items &amp; was selling them in Freeport at the time to raise the money.  Another friend of mine agreed to sell me an FBSS for 8k.  I needed a quick loan of about 6500 for a few hours.<br>
<br>
Remembering the advice to ask for help from fellow hawks, I posted a request in guild chat.<br>
<br>
I was shocked.  Probably the most upset I had been since joining the Hawks. I was SUMMARILY hushed by NUMEROUS requests that I NOT ask for money / loans in guildchat.  Mind you, I had fully explained the terms of my request for assistance - we are talkin a mere matter of hours - one day at the MOST before the amount would be repaid.<br>
<br>
So, you understand I hope, that I was livid from the frustration of being told / asked NOT to discuss the prospect of forming an active treasury and NOW asked / told &quot;drop it!&quot; when asking for help from fellow hawks - which is what I was ORIGINALLY advised to do. <br>
<br>
THIS is the EXACT Reason I proposed a bank in the FIRST place. To AVOID the level of .. rage having been advised two separate courses of action.  As it turned out, no Hawks were willing or perhaps able to help and all assistance came from people outside the guild. How very sad.  I would like to restate, we are not talking about a handout, I had sold an item worth well in excess of the 8k I needed - but needed the 6500 up front for a short while to take advantage of a 2k discount.<br>
<br>
SO - I would like add that my proposal for a community fund DID meet with some enthusiasm and I was asked to post my idea here.<br>
<br>
Here are the general guidelines I propose in CONCEPT:<br>
<br>
A Guild Fund / Bank / Treasury    ( call it what you like )<br>
<br>
Only members that wish to participate / donate can withdraw.  If  you don't like the idea - don't donate. This prevents 15 people from depositing and 2 from withdrawing all funds or vice versa.<br>
<br>
A 5 to 1 borrowing ratio.  You deposit 1k - you are qualified to withdraw 5k for a SHORT term.<br>
<br>
Length: Loans lasting less than a (week?) incur no interest.<br>
        Loans lasting 1-4 weeks incur simple 10% interest.<br>
        Weekly payments would be highly encouraged.<br>
        Payments / Withdrawals would be made generally during an established &quot;window&quot; of time.  <br>
        Special requests outside the normal 'window' of time would be at fund administrators' discretion.<br>
<br>
<br>
The person borrowing posts the amount and all subsequent related transactions on this webpage under the Guild Treasury heading which is ALREADY established !! <br>
<br>
Five officers (volunteers) who are on often and highly accessible would have access to a communal account which is PURCHASED for the express and sole purpose of running the account from Freeport.<br>
<br>
Items may be donated to the treasury by members who wish to participate.  They would be donated at 50% value (credit)and sold to guild members ONLY .....at a reduced market value.<br>
<br>
Any other ideas?<br>
<br>
My POLL question is: Does this subject warrant further discussion?</FONT><FORM method=post action="http://pub29.ezboard.com/fsilverhawksofdrinalfrm37.processVote?topicID=5.topic"><table border=0 cellpadding=3 cellspacing=0 width="55%"><tbody><tr><td><input type="radio" name="choice" value="1"><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>I like it - sounds great - let's do it!</FONT></td></tr><tr><td><input type="radio" name="choice" value="2"><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Great idea, but let's rehash the guidelines a bit.</FONT></td></tr><tr><td><input type="radio" name="choice" value="3"><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>If you guys want to form a fund, fine with me - but count me out.</FONT></td></tr><tr><td><input type="radio" name="choice" value="4"><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Not only will I not participate but I dont think anyone should.</FONT></td></tr><tr><td><input type="radio" name="choice" value="5"><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Nice weather we're having, isn't it?</FONT></td></tr></tbody></table><P><input type=submit value="Vote"><a HREF=http://pub29.ezboard.com/fsilverhawksofdrinalfrm37.showMessage?topicID=5.topic&pollResults=on><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Show results</FONT></A> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub29.ezboard.com/udawnbria.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DawnBria</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 92<br> <font color=#A0B0E0>(4/3/01 3:31:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub29.ezboard.com/fsilverhawksofdrinalfrm37.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Should we have an active Treasury - read the post!</span><hr size=1> Hay Konjur I am the one that voted see me, 6500pp ? a few hours Wow , show me where you can get 6500pp in a few hours i will join you had we can make 13000pp then you have your 6500 and I can get 6500pp to, It took me 2 weeks to make that kind of money at level 33 that along with HP helping, I am far from even a little rich I have some money and dream of money that can get me a FBSS or the likes.<br>
