Bria <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub29.ezboard.com/udawnbria.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DawnBria</A> at: 4/3/01 2:35:40 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#A0B0E0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub29.ezboard.com/uaguita.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aguita</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 528<br> <font color=#A0B0E0>(4/3/01 4:19:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub29.ezboard.com/fsilverhawksofdrinalfrm37.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Should we have an active Treasury - read the post!</span><hr size=1> Sorry, I'm greatly opposed to this idea.  First of all, who would fork out the $10 per month for an additional account?<br>
<br>
Who's going to keep track of all of this?  I would not wish *anything* like this for ANYONE... EQ takes up way too much time as it is.<br>
<br>
Also, I firmly believe, if you don't have the cash to buy it... then don't buy it.  Period.  <br>
<br>
What you're talking about is going to take away a LOT of time from people to keep track of this.. and the 5 officers like you'd say would have to log off... get on as the person... hand out the money.. make a note of this... or, get on, receive money..  No, we want to be in there helping the guild in other ways... Organizing Raids, helping on CRs, dealing with issues, helping with questions regarding guild with prospective members.  This takes a HUGE amount of time away from my hunting...  <br>
<br>
I am firmly against this idea... If you don't have the money, then don't buy it.. This isn't a democracy, it's an authoritian government with Darkarr as the leader.<br>
<br>
Although people are trustworthy in the Hawks, who's to say they will pay it back?  How would you enforce such a thing? interest? sorry, but I don't think that's a very good way.<br>
<br>
Also, who is to say who gets what money?  How do you determine one person's need over another?  If two people both need 5k and there is only 5k in the bank, do you loan to both? just one? Too easy for someone to get their feelings hurt.<br>
<br>
In my humble opinion, we are NOT a guild about loot or money.  If you want that, goto another guild.  We are about helping each other and standing up for what is right and true.  I firmly believe if you allow this to enter the guild, it will be a bad thing.  I firmly oppose this.   <p><FONT face=Arial,Helvetica,Geneva,Swiss,SunSans-Regular color=#191970 size=2>
