enFromWeb?topicID=5.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Should we have an active Treasury - read the post!</span><hr size=1> I agree with the above replies. I will not participate in a bank. On the surface it sounds great, but in EQ reality (oxymoron?) I don't think it will work.<br>
<br>
Gossimer. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#A0B0E0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub29.ezboard.com/uartimuss.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Artimuss</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 196<br> <font color=#A0B0E0>(4/4/01 7:14:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub29.ezboard.com/fsilverhawksofdrinalfrm37.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Maybe we should suggest ....</span><hr size=1> To Verant that they open a REAL BANK! (actually more of a pawn shop)  You put items up for collateral and you are able to drawn against those items... This way WE don't have to worry about it... We are ALL way to busy to play Monopoly Banker.   But Verant on the other hand.... <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rollin --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/roll.gif ALT=":rollin"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    Other than that idea, I say go hunt hill giants or uber rare drops.. At 1 point in time I had 5kpp.. but then I bought a Paw and it was all gone!  Nowadays, I keep just enough cash to survive on.  Someday when I get quad kiting I may be rich but I doubt it...<br>
