<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :hat --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/pimp.gif ALT=":hat"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub29.ezboard.com/utaluracwnzeylon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Talura cwnZeylon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 44<br> <font color=#A0B0E0>(4/4/01 10:26:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub29.ezboard.com/fsilverhawksofdrinalfrm37.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Maybe we should suggest ....</span><hr size=1> *shrug* As one of the people who offered to help out I also have to say I don't really support having a guild loanshark account for basically the same reasons as Aguita outlined: who wants the added headache of remembering who has money on loan, etc; as well as what happens when there are a few outstanding loans and someone else wants money? Well, they're SOL until at least part of the balance is repaid. I've loaned people sizable chunks of my income (have a friend I gave 1300 pp to so they could find a fang for EBW, which has not been paid back yet, another one borrowed about 2k for a few items, as well as a few sub-1k loans that I don't even recall), I don't like harassing people for money owed.<br>
As for the item, you can find FBSS' for sale at around 8.5 if you hunt around, they're almost common if you hit drinal's ezboard (well, ok, so not quite...) looking for a seller. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#A0B0E0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub29.ezboard.com/uanayazen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>AnayaZen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 136<br> <font color=#A0B0E0>(4/4/01 10:56:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub29.ezboard.com/fsilverhawksofdrinalfrm37.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Maybe we should suggest ....</span><hr size=1> I guess my feeling is that if you need to borrow that much money to get an item , the item is out of your reach.  I dont mind people asking to borrow a bit of money here and there... but 6.5K is a lot to ask. But I would much rather be asked in a private tell for a loan than asking in guild chat. <br>
<br>
I think the guild treasury section of the web was intended as a place for people to post any things that they have extra of ... using that for things like extra spells and gems is a great idea.  Using it for a &quot;bank&quot; would just be a pain for all involved.<br>
<br>
-Maila <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub29.ezboard.com/ustaveisland.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Staveisland</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Administrator</span><br>  Posts: 288<br> <font color=#A0B0E0>(4/4/01 11:35:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub29.ezboard.com/fsilverhawksofdrinalfrm37.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Maybe we should suggest ....</span><hr size=1> Do I think you were wrong for asking for 6500pp? Nope.  If you had no immediate means of repaying the money, I'd say it was not your time.  As you were simply a transaction or two from it, you had reason to ask and assure others you were worth it, just not liquid enough at the time.<br>
<br>
I think many were probably shocked at your asking because most just simply do not have that much money.  We may have had one or perhaps two people with that much cash.  We may have had a half dozen on at the time with 1k or more. I hope you'll take the reaction you got for what it was, which in my opinion was this: Most here want to help, and most here will lend a bit of money if they can, but many are not comfortable doing ANY lending and some not if it is THAT much.  Too many horror stories of people not getting paid back or getting scammed (and I don't believe anybody thinks you are capable of those).  Some folks worked very hard to get what they have and to loan it all away would be a tough thing.  Konjur, I'm sure you would loan that money to me if you had it and I asked and showed you how I knew I would have it back in a few hours.  I would have done the same for you.  Some will not lend that much money and while it may be frustrating, there is nothing wrong with them for being conservative.  It's understandable.<br>
 <br>
